[[Image:Assasingdsrty.jpg|right|thumb]]'''''Assassination Vacation''''' is a book by [[Sarah Vowell]], published in 2005, in which she travels around the United States researching the [[assassination]]s of [[President of the United States|U.S. Presidents]] [[Abraham Lincoln]], [[William McKinley]] and [[James Garfield]].<ref name="ref1">{{cite news|url=http://travel.nytimes.com/2005/05/15/travel/15armchair.html|title=New York Times Review of "Assassination Vacation"|accessdate=2011-12-20 | work=The New York Times|first=Richard B.|last=Woodward|date=2005-05-15}}</ref>  While most of the book is devoted to facts about the assassinated presidents and the men who would murder them, Vowell intersperses the book with anecdotes of her adventures on her self-proclaimed "[[pilgrimage]]" of presidential assassination. <ref name="ref2">{{cite web|url=http://books.simonandschuster.com/Assassination-Vacation/Sarah-Vowell/9780743550291|title=Simon & Schuster's "Assassination Vacation" Promo page|accessdate=2011-12-20}}</ref> 

==Audiobook==

An abridged audiobook was released by [[Simon & Schuster]] on March 29, 2005.<ref name="ref3">{{cite web|url=http://books.simonandschuster.com/Assassination-Vacation/Sarah-Vowell/9780743260046|title=Simon & Schuster's "Assassination Vacation" Audio Book Promo page|accessdate=2011-12-20}}</ref>  It contained a large cast of readers, and original music was composed by [[Michael Giacchino]]. In order of appearance, the cast was:

*[[Conan O'Brien]] as [[Robert Todd Lincoln]] 
*[[Eric Bogosian]] as [[John Wilkes Booth]]
*[[Stephen King]] as [[Abraham Lincoln]]
*[[Dave Eggers]] as Mike Ryan
*[[Catherine Keener]] as [[Gretchen Worden]]
*[[Jon Stewart]] as [[James A. Garfield]]
*[[Tony Kushner]] as [[John Humphrey Noyes]]
*[[Brad Bird]] as [[Charles Guiteau]] and [[Emma Goldman]]
*[[Daniel Handler]] as [[William McKinley]]
*[[Greg Giraldo]] as [[Theodore Roosevelt]]
*[[David Rakoff]] as [[Leon Czolgosz]]

As mentioned above, Brad Bird was part of the cast; he wrote and directed the film ''[[The Incredibles]]'', in which author Vowell had a [[The_Incredibles#Cast|voice-acting part]]. Michael Giacchino, composer for ''The Incredibles'', composed the music for the audiobook.

